</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="193A36E4FF810456ECA8FF60FF018A7D" blockId="24.[150,1437,152,2034]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
Plant epiphytic, flowering ca. 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FF810456EE36FF60FD9D8FF5" box="[521,609,152,178]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="cm" value="110.0">110 cm</quantity>
high, propagating by basal shoots. Leaves 20–30, densely rosulate, arcuate, forming a broad funnelform rosette; sheaths elliptic, ca. 13 × 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FF810456EFE0FF46FBCF8F9F" box="[991,1075,190,216]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="cm" value="8.5">8.5 cm</quantity>
, densely brown lepidote, dark castaneous near the base, paler toward the apex; blades long linear, rounded to subacute and minutely apiculate, 32–50 × 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FF810456ED45FEF4FDFD8E61" box="[378,513,268,294]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.1" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="3.7" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="cm" value="4.1" valueMax="4.5" valueMin="3.7">3.7–4.5 cm</quantity>
, not narrowed at the base, finely nerved, glaucous-green, inconspicuously and sparsely white lepidote to glabrescent, covered by white wax mainly abaxially. Peduncle 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FF810456E895FECAFAE28E0B" box="[1194,1310,306,332]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="cm" value="55.0" valueMax="60.0" valueMin="50.0">50–60 cm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FF810456E957FECAFF1B8E34" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="cm" value="0.6" valueMax="0.7" valueMin="0.5">0.5– 0.7 cm</quantity>
in diameter, erect, green, glabrous, sulcate when drying; peduncle bracts the basal ones subfoliaceous, the upper ones ovate-lanceolate, acuminate, enfolding the peduncle at the base but not completely concealing it, erect except for the the suberect apex, glaucous-green, glabrescent, the basal ones distinctly surpassing the internodes, the upper ones equaling to distinctly shorter than the internodes. Inflorescence paniculate, laxly once-branched, 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FF810456ED65FE0CFE2E8D49" box="[346,466,500,526]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="cm" value="45.0" valueMax="60.0" valueMin="30.0">30–60 cm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FF810456EE1DFE0CFD668D49" box="[546,666,500,526]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="cm" value="20.0" valueMax="25.0" valueMin="15.0">15–25 cm</quantity>
in diameter, erect; primary bracts broadly subtriangular-ovate, acute and apiculate, 2.3–2.5 x 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FF810456EDC1FDE2FDC78D73" box="[510,571,538,564]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="cm" value="2.0">2 cm</quantity>
, stramineous, glabrescent, distinctly shorter than the stipes; branches 4 to 9 (including the terminal one), the lateral ones 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FF810456EEEEFDB9FCB48D1C" box="[721,840,577,603]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" metricValueMax="2.2" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="cm" value="18.0" valueMax="22.0" valueMin="14.0">14–22 cm</quantity>
long, densely flowered at anthesis, with 11 to 23 flowers; stipes 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FF810456ED61FD90FE468DC5" box="[350,442,616,642]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="cm" value="5.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="4.0">4–7 cm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FF810456EE33FD90FD6B8DC5" box="[524,663,616,642]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="cm" value="0.4" valueMax="0.5" valueMin="0.3">0.3–0.5 cm</quantity>
in diameter, glabrous, green, bearing 2 to 4 suberect to erect, carinate, sterile bracts; rachis geniculate, green, glabrous; internodes 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FF810456EFF9FD76FBCB8DEF" box="[966,1079,654,680]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" metricValueMax="12.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="8.0" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="4.0">4–12 mm</quantity>
long, ca. 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FF810456E893FD76FAF98DEF" box="[1196,1285,654,680]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="0.3">0.3 mm</quantity>
in diameter; the terminal branch 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FF810456EDB8FD4DFE028D88" box="[391,510,693,719]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.55" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.1" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="cm" value="25.5" valueMax="30.0" valueMin="21.0">21–30 cm</quantity>
long, with 16 to 27 flowers, its stipe 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FF810456EF80FD4DFBCA8D88" box="[959,1078,693,719]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="cm" value="11.5" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="10.0">10–13 cm</quantity>
long, bearing 4 to 6 ecarinate sterile bracts distinctly shorter than the internodes; floral bracts broadly subtriangular, narrowly obtuse, 12–16 × 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FF810456EC8FFCFAFEC88C5B" box="[176,308,770,796]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="11.5" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="10.0">10–13 mm</quantity>
, distichous, suberect, not imbricate and exposing the rachis, slightly secund with the flowers, stramineous at anthesis, inconspicuously brown lepidote inside, not fully enfolding the sepals and about reaching 1/3 to 1/2 of their length, the basal ones carinate, the upper ones obtusely if at all carinate, apex straight to slightly incurved. Flowers nocturnal, producing a weak garlic odor, sublaxly arranged, slightly divergent or suberect before anthesis, strongly downwardly secund at anthesis, 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FF810456E808FC65FB498CF0" box="[1079,1205,925,951]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.65" metricValueMax="2.7" metricValueMin="2.6" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="26.5" valueMax="27.0" valueMin="26.0">26–27 mm</quantity>
long (including the petals), pedicels 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FF810456ED63FC3CFE418C99" box="[348,445,964,990]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4–5 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FF810456EE36FC3CFD978C99" box="[521,619,964,990]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5–6 mm</quantity>
in diameter, green, glabrous; sepals oblong-ovate to subelliptic, apex subacute to acute, 16–17 × 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FF810456EDE3FC12FDBD8B43" box="[476,577,1002,1028]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="8.5" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="8.0">8–9 mm</quantity>
, cymbiform, subdensely and very inconspicuously white lepidote inside, ecarinate, green, nerved mainly toward the apex, becoming stramineous at the apex; petals obovate to spatulate, apex emarginate, 20–23 × 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FF810456EE78FBC0FD478B15" box="[583,699,1080,1106]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" metricValueMax="1.2" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="10.5" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="9.0">9–12 mm</quantity>
, connate at the base for 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FF810456EFE7FBC0FBC08B15" box="[984,1084,1080,1106]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4 mm</quantity>
, yellowish or sometimes with purplish-wine spots concentrated near the apex, suberect to nearly spreading at anthesis and forming a campanulate corolla ca. 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FF810456ED86FB7DFDF18BD8" box="[441,525,1157,1183]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="15.0">15 mm</quantity>
in diameter at the apex; bearing 2 narrowly lanceolate, acuminate to shortly bidentate appendages at the base, 8–11 × 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FF810456EEBEFB54FD008B81" box="[641,764,1196,1222]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="2.25" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="2.0">2–2.5 mm</quantity>
, adnate to the petals for ca. 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FF810456E879FB54FB728B81" box="[1094,1166,1196,1222]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
. Stamens included and radially arranged; anthers sublinear-sagittate, apex apiculate, 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FF810456EF45FB2AFC218BAB" box="[890,989,1234,1260]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5–6 mm</quantity>
long; stigma convolute-bladed, ca. 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FF810456E9B2FB2AFF398A54" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
in diameter, shortly papillose, pale yellow to apically wine colored; ovules shortly caudate. Capsules unkown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="519F656FFF810456ECF9FABEFB578965" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="193A36E4FF810456ECF9FABEFB578965" blockId="24.[150,1437,152,2034]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis id="2BF1EAF6FF810456ECF9FABEFDFD8A27" bold="true" box="[198,513,1350,1376]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Distribution and habitat</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName id="DE854D67FF810456EE19FABFFCF28A27" authorityName="Leme" authorityYear="2011" box="[550,782,1351,1376]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Vriesea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="minutiflora">
<emphasis id="2BF1EAF6FF810456EE19FABFFCF28A27" box="[550,782,1351,1376]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Vriesea minutiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a typical understory epiphyte of the hygrophilous Atlantic Forest of 
<collectingRegion id="DB41F806FF810456ED4EFA95FE458AC0" box="[369,441,1389,1415]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, on the higher spots on the mountains elevations of 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FF810456E81AFA95FB3B8AC0" box="[1061,1223,1389,1415]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.75" metricValueMax="9.5" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="m" value="875.0" valueMax="950.0" valueMin="800.0">
800 to 
<specimenCount id="0F83FD6DFF810456E846FA95FB3B8AC0" box="[1145,1223,1389,1415]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="generic">950 m</specimenCount>
</quantity>
. It is known from two difference places (i.e., 
<typeStatus id="C63E8846FF810456EDE4FA6CFDBF8AE9" box="[475,579,1428,1454]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">holotype</typeStatus>
and 
<typeStatus id="C63E8846FF810456EE41FA6CFD188AE9" box="[638,740,1428,1454]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">paratype</typeStatus>
locations) which have similar bromeliad flora represented by 
<taxonomicName id="DE854D67FF810456EC82FA43FDF78A93" authority="Mez" authorityName="Mez" authorityYear="1892" box="[189,523,1466,1492]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Aechmea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="turbinocalyx">
<emphasis id="2BF1EAF6FF810456EC82FA43FE368A93" box="[189,458,1467,1492]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Aechmea turbinocalyx</emphasis>
Mez
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="DE854D67FF810456EE26FA43FCA08A93" authority="Brongn." authorityName="Brongn." box="[537,860,1466,1492]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Billbergia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="morelii">
<emphasis id="2BF1EAF6FF810456EE26FA43FD0C8A93" box="[537,752,1467,1492]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Billbergia morelii</emphasis>
Brongn.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="DE854D67FF810456EF55FA43FB598A93" authority="Leme" authorityName="Leme" authorityYear="1993" box="[874,1189,1466,1492]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Canistrum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="auratum">
<emphasis id="2BF1EAF6FF810456EF55FA43FBAA8A93" box="[874,1110,1467,1492]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Canistrum auratum</emphasis>
Leme
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="DE854D67FF810456E88CFA43FE998ABC" authority="(E. Pereira) Leme" authorityName="Leme" baseAuthorityName="E. Pereira" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Nidularium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis id="2BF1EAF6FF810456E88CFA43FA678A93" box="[1203,1435,1467,1492]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Nidularium bicolor</emphasis>
(E.Pereira) Leme
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="DE854D67FF810456ED4EFA19FC0B8ABC" authority="(Griseb.) M. A. Spencer &amp; L. B. Sm." authorityName="M. A. Spencer &amp; L. B. Sm." baseAuthorityName="Griseb." box="[369,1015,1505,1531]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Racinaea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spiculosa">
<emphasis id="2BF1EAF6FF810456ED4EFA19FDAA8ABD" box="[369,598,1505,1530]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Racinaea spiculosa</emphasis>
(Griseb.) M.A.Spencer &amp; L.B.Sm.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="DE854D67FF810456E83BFA19FAC58ABC" authority="Leme" authorityName="Leme" authorityYear="2003" box="[1028,1337,1505,1531]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Ronnbergia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="silvana">
<emphasis id="2BF1EAF6FF810456E83BFA19FB168ABD" box="[1028,1258,1505,1530]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Ronnbergia silvana</emphasis>
Leme
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="DE854D67FF810456E97BFA19FE738965" authority="Leme" authorityName="Leme" authorityYear="2005" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Vriesea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="blackburniana">
<emphasis id="2BF1EAF6FF810456E97BFA19FEBE8966" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Vriesea blackburniana</emphasis>
Leme
