<paragraph id="193A36E4FF810457ECF9F95AFC768FB8" blockId="24.[150,1437,152,2034]" lastBlockId="25.[151,1435,152,255]" lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="26" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis id="2BF1EAF6FF810456ECF9F95AFE9089FB" bold="true" box="[198,364,1698,1724]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Observations</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName id="DE854D67FF810456EDADF95BFD8989FB" authorityName="Leme" authorityYear="2011" box="[402,629,1699,1724]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Vriesea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="minutiflora">
<emphasis id="2BF1EAF6FF810456EDADF95BFD8989FB" box="[402,629,1699,1724]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Vriesea minutiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a member of section 
<taxonomicName id="DE854D67FF810456EFB2F95BFAB389FB" authority="(E. Morren) Wawra ex Wittm." authorityName="Wittm." baseAuthorityName="E. Morren" box="[909,1359,1698,1724]" class="Liliopsida" family="Iridaceae" genus="Xiphion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2BF1EAF6FF810456EFB2F95BFC1689FB" box="[909,1002,1699,1724]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Xiphion</emphasis>
(E.Morren) Wawra ex Wittm.
</taxonomicName>
, being most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="DE854D67FF810456ED71F931FCE489A4" authority="Leme (1993: 2)" authorityName="Leme" authorityPageNumber="2" authorityYear="1993" box="[334,792,1737,1763]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Vriesea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="ruschii" subSpecies="leonii">
<emphasis id="2BF1EAF6FF810456ED71F931FE4089A5" box="[334,444,1737,1762]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">V. ruschii</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="2BF1EAF6FF810456EE2AF931FDA489A5" box="[533,600,1737,1762]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">leonii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="7D144B15FF810456EE60F931FCE489A4" author="Leme, E. M. C." box="[607,792,1737,1763]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="1 - 12" refId="ref22272" refString="Leme, E. M. C. (1993) Novas Bromeliaceas Nativas do Brasil - IX. Pabstia 4 (1): 1 - 12." type="journal article" year="1993">Leme (1993: 2)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which is a taxon currently under study to reevaluate it and elevate its status to species rank (Leme unpubl.). The morphological differences to be highlighted in comparison with the latter are: the arcuate leaves (vs. suberect), comparatively longer inflorescence (
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FF810456E96FF8EEFF478810" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="cm" value="45.0" valueMax="60.0" valueMin="30.0">30–60 cm</quantity>
vs. 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FF810456ECCFF8C5FE958810" box="[240,361,1853,1879]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="cm" value="27.5" valueMax="35.0" valueMin="20.0">20–35 cm</quantity>
long), bearing lateral branches with more numerous flowers (11–23 vs. 8–15 flowers), stramineous floral bracts (vs. pale green) with the basal ones carinate (vs. ecarinate) and smaller (12–16 × 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FF810456E94FF89CFF1488E3" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="11.5" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="10.0">10– 13 mm</quantity>
vs. ca. 20 × 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FF810456ED41F872FE2988E3" box="[382,469,1930,1956]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="18.0">18 mm</quantity>
), smaller flowers (26–27 vs. 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FF810456EF16F872FC8788E3" box="[809,891,1930,1956]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="35.0">35 mm</quantity>
long), smaller sepals (16–17 × 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FF810456E8D1F872FAB788E3" box="[1262,1355,1930,1956]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="8.5" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="8.0">8-9 mm</quantity>
vs. ca. 20 × 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FF810456ECEBF849FED0888C" box="[212,300,1969,1995]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="12.0">12 mm</quantity>
), and also by the smaller petals (20–23 × 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FF810456EF26F849FC75888C" box="[793,905,1969,1995]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" metricValueMax="1.2" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="10.5" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="9.0">9–12 mm</quantity>
vs. ca. 28 × 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FF810456E81DF849FB85888C" box="[1058,1145,1969,1995]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="13.0">13 mm</quantity>
). On the other hand, this new species can be associated to 
<taxonomicName id="DE854D67FF810456EE1AF820FC6D88B5" authority="Smith (1960: 255)" authorityName="Smith" authorityPageNumber="255" authorityYear="1960" box="[549,913,2008,2034]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Vriesea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cearensis">
<emphasis id="2BF1EAF6FF810456EE1AF820FD4F88B6" box="[549,691,2008,2033]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">V. cearensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="7D144B15FF810456EE84F820FC6D88B5" author="Smith, L. B." box="[699,913,2008,2034]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="249 - 257" refId="ref23572" refString="Smith, L. B. (1960) Notes on Bromeliaceae XV. Phytologia. 7 (5): 249 - 257." type="journal article" year="1960">Smith (1960:255)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, differing by the acuminate peduncle bracts (vs. rounded and minutely apiculate), longer inflorescence (30–60 vs. 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FF800457EFCDFF60FB968FF5" box="[1010,1130,152,178]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" unit="cm" value="22.5" valueMax="25.0" valueMin="20.0">20–25 cm</quantity>
long) with longer lateral branches (14–22 vs. 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FF800457EDB1FF46FE098F9F" box="[398,501,190,216]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" unit="cm" value="11.0" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="9.0">9–13 cm</quantity>
long) and more numerous flowers per branch (11–23 vs. 4–9 flowers), and by the larger petals appendages (8–11 × 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FF800457EE74FF1DFD3D8FB8" box="[587,705,229,255]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" unit="mm" value="2.25" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="2.0">2–2.5 mm</quantity>
vs. 6 × 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FF800457EF20FF1DFC828FB8" box="[799,894,229,255]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
).
</paragraph>
